  "text": "2. Background. As mentioned before, most of the penalized variable selection procedures share the same form of penalty function and differ only by the value of penalization coefficient, λ. They can be divided into three groups: (1) constant λ: forward selection (or backward elimination) with fixed p-to-enter (p-to-drop) where λ = z 2 (p−to−enter)/2 ; AIC [CITATION_1] ] and Cp [Mallows (1973) ] where λ = 2 ≈ z 2 0.16/2 ; (2) λ m that is the function of the size of the set of variables m over which the model is searched, for example the universal threshold of Donoho and Jonhstone. Note that the latter can also be viewed as a multiple testing Bonferroni procedure at level ",
